resources.string: Numerical Reasoning - Knowing how to read data and interpret statistics.
Negotiating - bargaining with others to solve a problem or reach an agreement.
Public Speaking- addressing or delivering a speech to a group or audience.
Reading - Following written instructions on what to do or how to operate a piece of equipment.
Listening - paying attention to what the other person is saying and responding appropriately.
Communication - being able to talk to strangers in ordinary conversational settings.
Explaining - speaking carefully and clearly so people can understand you quickly and easily.
Measuring -Using equipment to determine surface area and volume measurements.
Questioning - asking the right questions to get useful information from others or to help them gain insight.
Budgeting- Deciding what to buy and how much to spend,to get work done at the lowest cost.
Calculation -Using basic arithmetic skills including adding, subtracting, multiplication and division
Writing - Being able to express yourself or explain things in writing.
